headline: Tech’s AI Push Risks a Bond Market Blowback: Credit Weekly
summary: Microsoft Corp., Oracle Corp. and other “hyperscalers” are in an arms race to invest in AI and beat competitors in a technology that could change vast parts of the economy.  Google parent Alphabet Inc. said it’s poised to spend as much as $185 billion on data centers this year, more than it has invested in the past three years combined.  Amazon.com Inc. promised an even bigger outlay: $200 billion.
